Package: dataforge
Title: Simulate Structured Data for Factorial and Mixed Designs
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Sagar", "S", email = "sagars314@protom.me", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides a comprehensive toolkit for simulating structured datasets 
    with user-specified means, standard deviations, and correlation structures. 
    Supports factorial designs (between-subjects, within-subjects, mixed), 
    correlated multivariate normal data, simulation from existing data frames, 
    mixed effects structures, contrast coding, distribution conversions, 
    and Likert-scale generation. Designed for researchers, educators, and data 
    scientists who need reproducible synthetic datasets for power analysis, 
    teaching, or testing statistical workflows.
